{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8fef9df8-182f-4a94-81f6-c6f1f110657b","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, **file compilation order matters** — files can only reference types/modules from files listed *above* them in the `.fsproj`. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_g7oajdwdQGvfemi8puZw8N","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-326cc6ebf79e49178982baeae40d024a/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-326cc6ebf79e49178982baeae40d024a/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"619d7dbf-5b22-446c-8480-8f2c982d3bb9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), and `Program.fs` depends on both. So `Domain.fs` must come first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the `<Compile>` items in the `.fsproj` file.","outputTokens":463,"requestId":"F03B:A64D3:453ADBF:4CE0A2A:69F9B07D"},"id":"c191d372-8c27-48d0-9174-171087254928","timestamp":"2026-05-05T08:55:33.843Z","parentId":"01f8f397-9b3e-4fcf-90e9-d990c9e4b2ac"}
